content:
You are given a dataset containing information about various cities and their corresponding crime rates and pollution levels. Your task is to analyze the correlation between these two variables and plot the results in a scatter plot using MATLAB.
To do this, you can use the following MATLAB code:
corr_coeff = corrcoef(data.crime_rate, data.pollution_level);
scatter(data.crime_rate, data.pollution_level);
title('Scatter plot of crime rate and pollution level with correlation coefficient: ' + string(corr_coeff(1,2)));
xlabel('Crime Rate');
ylabel('Pollution Level');
Can you explain what the correlation coefficient represents in this context and how to interpret it?
